In his weekly address, President Trump expresses his sympathy and support for the victims of Hurricane Harvey. He thanks the first responders, volunteers, and organizations for their efforts in assisting those affected by the storm. The President states that federal aid is available for recovery efforts in Texas and Louisiana, and emphasizes the unity and resilience of the American people in times of crisis. He reassures the affected communities that the nation stands with them and will help in the recovery and rebuilding process.